HEADWORD: Ronde
<hw>Ronde</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.]</ety>
<fld>(Print.)</fld> <def>A kind of script in which the heavy strokes are
nearly upright, giving the characters when taken together a round
look.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Rondeau</ent>⟦br⟧
